ps%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feveryone-talking-about-ai-plenty-clearly-dont-understand-davos-wef-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorld%20Economic%20Forum%20in%20Davos%3C%2Fa%3E%20explained%20how%20they%20convinced%20their%20employees.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20are%20increasingly%20looking%20for%20ways%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgenerative-ai-era-important-skills-jobs-leaders-davos-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euse%20AI%20to%20improve%20their%20business%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20change%20is%20hard%20and%20not%20all%20employees%20are%20excited%20about%20learning%20a%20new%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%2031%25%20of%20organizations%20reported%20that%20employees%20are%20reluctant%20or%20even%20outright%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-generational-divide-millennials-boomers-gen-z-technology-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresistant%20to%20using%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Cisco%20AI%20Readiness%20Index.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cisco.com%2Fc%2Fdam%2Fm%2Fen_us%2Fsolutions%2Fai%2Freadiness-index%2Fdocuments%2Fcisco-global-ai-readiness-index.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20November%2C%20it%20surveyed%20over%208%2C000%20business%20leaders%20in%20organizations%20with%20more%20than%20500%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20some%2097%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20that%20the%20sense%20of%20urgency%20to%20use%20AI-powered%20technologies%20has%20increased%20at%20their%20companies%20in%20the%20last%206%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20how%20should%20employers%20get%20their%20employees%20on%20board%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompany%20leaders%20at%20the%20World%20Economic%20Forum%20told%20Business%20Insider%20there's%20one%20simple%20thing%20bosses%20can%20do%3A%20be%20clear%20about%20what%20you%20want%20to%20use%20AI%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStart%20with%20use%20cases%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Liz%20Centoni%2C%20chief%20strategy%20officer%20and%20general%20manager%20of%20applications%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcisco-ai-cloud-market-ai-equipment-sales-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECisco%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECentoni%20suggests%20outlining%20the%20potential%20benefits%20of%20using%20AI%20and%20providing%20specific%20examples%20of%20how%20it%20might%20be%20used.%20A%20big%20reason%20AI%20has%20caught%20on%20strongly%20across%20different%20teams%20at%20her%20company%2C%20she%20says%2C%20is%20because%20there%20are%20many%20different%20clearly%20defined%20use%20cases%20for%20the%20tech%20that%20are%20making%20people's%20jobs%20easier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJeff%20Maggioncalda%2C%20CEO%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Flearning%2Fwhat-is-coursera%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECoursera%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20says%20it's%20important%20to%20explain%20to%20employees%20how%20AI%20might%20make%20their%20jobs%20better%20or%20more%20enjoyable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20workers%20are%20understandably%20afraid%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwill-ai-replace-jobs-generative-artificial-intelligence-tools-training-ceos-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeing%20replaced%20by%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Maggioncalda%20says%20it%20can%20be%20helpful%20to%20frame%20the%20inclusion%20of%20AI%20as%20augmentation%20rather%20than%20automation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20things%20that%20the%20technology%20is%20really%20good%20at%20are%20the%20kinds%20of%20things%20that%20people%20don't%20like%2C%26quot%3B%20Maggioncalda%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20suggests%20framing%20the%20AI%20experimentation%20as%20an%20adventure%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20be%20more%20productive%2C%20free%20up%20time%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Benjoy%20your%20job%20more.%26quot%3B%20By%20pushing%20into%20that%20new%20frontier%2C%20employees%20will%20ideally%20grow%20and%20create%20more%20opportunities%20for%20themselves%2C%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaul%20Knopp%2C%20CEO%20of%20KPMG%2C%20says%20that%20his%20company%20emphasizes%20to%20employees%20that%20while%20integrating%20and%20adapting%20to%20emerging%20technologies%20might%20change%20employee%20roles%2C%20historically%20it's%20resulted%20in%20a%20net%20growth%20in%20the%20workforce.%20And%20over%20time%2C%20he%20says%20he%20expects%20AI%20to%20lead%20to%20both%20revenue%20growth%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-jobs-al-will-create-no-collegee-degree-chatgpt-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrowth%20in%20the%20workforce%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20expect%20it%20to%20be%20true%20of%20generative%20AI%20too%2C%20not%20just%20because%20you%20need%20people%20to%20create%20the%20generative%20AI%20solutions%2C%20which%20requires%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20and%20effort%2C%20but%20you%20need%20the%20people%20to%20ensure%20that%20it%20can%20be%20trusted%2C%26quot%3B%20Knopp%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20thing%20that%20seems%20to%20resonate%20with%20people%2C%20Knopp%20says%2C%20is%20telling%20employees%20%26quot%3Byou%20think%20it%20will%20make%20their%20jobs%20ultimately%20more%20interesting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20while%20it's%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20address%20employee%20concerns%20about%20how%20their%20work%20may%20change%20due%20to%20the%20new%20technology%2C%20those%20at%20Davos%20are%20betting%20that%20pitching%20staff%20on%20specifically%20how%20that%20change%20can%20be%20positive%20%E2%80%94%20hopefully%20making%20them%20happier%20and%20more%20effective%20in%20their%20job%20%E2%80%94%20to%20get%20their%20buy-in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-employees-to-use-ai-at-work-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706001721000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A