%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Flawyer-jai-anant-dehadrai-summoned-by-cbi-in-mahua-moitra-case-4916005%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Manipur%3A%20CM%20Biren%20Singh%20Confirms%20Imposition%20of%20Article%20355%2C%20Draws%20Flak%20Over%20Secrecy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30163218%2FFwqAt6VXsAIGp1_.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20delegation%20of%20senior%20officials%20from%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20(MHA)%20and%20Intelligence%20Bureau%20(IB)%20arrived%20in%20Imphal%20on%20Monday%20(January%2022)%20to%20hold%20discussions%20aimed%20at%20restoring%20peace%20and%20normalcy%20in%20Manipur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20officials%20will%20hold%20consultations%20with%20the%20state%20government%2C%20community%20leaders%2C%20and%20other%20stakeholders%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fmha-officials-in-manipur-to-hold-talks-with-govt-stakeholders%2Farticleshow%2F107061571.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ecompile%20a%20comprehensive%20list%20of%20demand%3C%2Fa%3Es%20that%20have%20been%20put%20forth%20by%20each%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20major%20point%20of%20contention%20is%20the%20hill%20tribe%E2%80%99s%20demand%20for%20the%20separation%20of%20administration%20from%20the%20valley%20and%20the%20removal%20of%20chief%20minister%20N.%20Biren%20Singh.%20However%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20has%20refused%20to%20entertain%20these%20demands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20various%20organisations%2C%20including%20Meira%20Paibis%20(women%20vigilantes)%2C%20organised%20massive%20protests%20demanding%20that%20the%20Union%20hand%20over%20the%20charge%20of%20Unified%20Command%20to%20the%20chief%20minister%20and%20remove%20security%20adviser%20and%20the%20command%E2%80%99s%20chairman%20Kuldiep%20Singh%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20name%20was%20missing%20from%20the%20list%20of%20names%20who%20are%20part%20of%20the%20Unified%20Command%20which%20sparked%20rumours%20that%20Article%20355%20of%20the%20constitution%20was%20in%20effect%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArticle%20355%20in%20Manipur%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20chief%20minister%20Biren%20Singh%20laid%20rumours%20to%20rest%20and%20revealed%2C%20at%20an%20all-party%20meeting%2C%20that%20Article%20355%20has%20been%20in%20effect%20in%20the%20state%20since%20the%20clashes%20broke%20out%20in%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELeaders%20at%20the%20all-party%20meeting%20from%20the%20opposition%20criticised%20the%20Union%20and%20the%20state%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Farticle-355-a-step-away-from-presidents-rule-in-manipur-now-opposition-4910110%5C%22%3Efor%20not%20revealing%20this%20to%20the%20public%20sooner.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20reflects%20the%20insincerity%20of%20both%20the%20Centre%20and%20the%20state%20government%2C%E2%80%9D%20Manipur%20Congress%20chief%20Meghachandra%20Singh%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20chief%20minister%20told%20us%20Article%20355%20has%20been%20enforced%20in%20Manipur.%20There%20was%20no%20clarity%20on%20this%20before.%20It%20is%20unfortunate%20that%20the%20chief%20minister%20took%20so%20long%20to%20tell%20us%20this.%20Both%20the%20Union%20and%20the%20state%20government%20are%20not%20sincere%2C%20we%20know%20now%2C%20it%20is%20confirmed%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Farticle-355-a-step-away-from-presidents-rule-in-manipur-now-opposition-4910110%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20reporters%20in%20Imphal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%20355%20mandates%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20safeguard%20states%20against%20external%20aggression%20and%20internal%20disturbance.%20This%20provision%20grants%20the%20Union%20the%20authority%20to%20assume%20control%20of%20a%20state%E2%80%99s%20law%20and%20order%20enforcement%20without%20dismissing%20the%20state%20government%20and%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20step%20below%20the%20President%E2%80%99s%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kuki-Zo%20tribes%20have%20been%20demanding%20President%E2%80%99s%20rule%20in%20Manipur.%20They%20say%20that%20President%E2%80%99s%20rule%20will%20ensure%20neutrality%20of%20security%20forces%20and%20government%20policies.%20However%2C%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20told%20parliament%20last%20year%20the%20state%20government%20was%20cooperating%20and%20there%20was%20no%20need%20for%20President%E2%80%99s%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMystery%20over%20Article%20355%20since%20last%20year%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20May%20last%20year%2C%20two%20public%20officials%20from%20the%20state%20%E2%80%93%20an%20elected%20MLA%20and%20head%20of%20the%20state%20police%20%E2%80%93%20had%20indicated%20that%20Article%20355%20had%20been%20imposed%20in%20Manipur.%20However%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fthe-mysterious-case-of-the-imposition-of-article-355-in-manipur%5C%22%3Eno%20formal%20order%20had%20been%20issued%20by%20the%20Union%20government%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20impose%20or%20invoke%20the%20constitutional%20provision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20in%20August%20last%20year%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmanipur-centre-says-no-information-on-article-355%5C%22%3EUnion%20home%20ministry%20categorically%20stated%20that%20it%20had%20no%20information%20on%20any%20notification%3C%2Fa%3E%20issued%20by%20the%20Union%20under%20Article%20355%20of%20the%20Constitution%20between%20January%202023%20and%20June%2013%2C%202023.%20The%20ministry%20was%20responding%20to%20a%20Right%20to%20Information%20(RTI)%20query%20filed%20by%20Karnataka%20high%20court%20advocate%20Ajay%20Kumar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20secrecy%20surrounding%20its%20imposition%20raises%20concerns%20because%20such%20a%20decision%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fthe-mysterious-case-of-the-imposition-of-article-355-in-manipur%5C%22%3Emade%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20legal%2C%20published%20announcement%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20be%20considered%20unlawful.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%20355%20is%20found%20in%20part%20XVIII%20of%20the%20Indian%20constitution%20which%20contains%20emergency%20provisions%20that%20are%20meant%20to%20be%20used%20in%20extremely%20rare%20circumstances.%20This%20section%20of%20the%20constitution%20empowers%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20declare%20a%20state%20of%20emergency%20(through%20Article%20352)%20or%2C%20in%20other%20cases%2C%20President%E2%80%99s%20Rule%20in%20a%20particular%20state%20of%20the%20Union%20(through%20Article%20356).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%20355%2C%20as%20it%20currently%20exists%2C%20was%20not%20in%20the%201948%20draft%20constitution%2C%20and%20was%20only%20added%20in%20September%201949%20(as%20draft%20Article%20277A).%20It%20was%20inserted%20with%20the%20objective%20of%20providing%20a%20legitimate%20ground%20for%20the%20application%20of%20Article%20356%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20which%20allows%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20issue%20a%20proclamation%20of%20President%E2%80%99s%20Rule%20in%20a%20specific%20state.%20Because%20imposing%20President%E2%80%99s%20Rule%20in%20a%20state%20is%20considered%20an%20extreme%20measure%2C%20the%20drafters%20of%20the%20constitution%20felt%20this%20insertion%20was%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20be%20noted%20that%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmanipur-centre-says-no-information-on-article-355%5C%22%3E%20Article%20355%20has%20never%20been%20imposed%20on%20a%20state%20without%20Article%20356%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Indian%20political%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705998331000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30