0phase%2C%20which%20examines%20legal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.postofficehorizoninquiry.org.uk%2Fpublic-hearings-timeline%5C%22%3Eaction%20against%20sub-postmasters%20and%20others%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20is%20arguably%20the%20most%20politicised%20and%20significant%20part%20of%20the%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELessons%20to%20be%20learned%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPublic%20inquiries%20are%20meant%20to%20take%20the%20heat%20out%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fheinonline.org%2FHOL%2FP%3Fh%3Dhein.journals%2Fmodlr52%26i%3D488%5C%22%3Ehighly%20politicised%20issues%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20examine%20matters%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Fpdf%2F10.1177%2F0170840604038182%5C%22%3Eorderly%20and%20objective%3C%2Fa%3E%20way.%20This%20new%20public%20awareness%20of%20the%20scandal%20therefore%20presents%20several%20challenges%20for%20the%20inquiry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20final%20stage%20of%20the%20inquiry%E2%80%99s%20proceedings%20being%20subject%20to%20greater%20scrutiny%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20consequential.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20name%20suggests%2C%20inquiries%20are%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1080%2F09649069.2023.2243137%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DIn%2520contrast%2520to%2520the%2520civil%2C%2527parties%2527%2520to%2520an%2520inquiry.%5C%22%3Easking%20questions%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20learning%20lessons.%20Above%20all%20else%2C%20they%20are%20intended%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instituteforgovernment.org.uk%2Farticle%2Fexplainer%2Fpublic-inquiries%5C%22%3Eprevent%20reoccurrence%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20mistakes%20and%20injustices%2C%20rather%20than%20being%20consumed%20by%20discussions%20of%20blame.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20the%20role%20of%20media%20coverage%2C%20which%20instead%20highlights%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1177%2F1362480616645648%3Fcasa_token%3DT1GEgAaZ3JUAAAAA%253A09cwzhJmAFj3oIlbzAXM-TJNK1C4LhBmJnHAb2-2ayWGu1v2K7pye4ygbM9ILnpkqdoS2xuA_qQ%5C%22%3Escandalised%20nature%20of%20issues%20under%20inquiry%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Issues%20of%20blame%20and%20culpability%2C%20and%20the%20testimony%20and%20conduct%20of%20individual%20witnesses%20are%20therefore%20the%20focus%20of%20headlines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20can%20mean%20that%2C%20when%20inquiries%20release%20their%20reports%2C%20public%20focus%20is%20on%20whether%20people%20have%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublications.parliament.uk%2Fpa%2Fcm200304%2Fcmselect%2Fcmpubadm%2F606%2F4111110.htm%5C%22%3Egot%20off%20alright%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20report%2C%20or%20have%20been%20criticised.%20A%20focus%20on%20these%20aspects%20risks%20overshadowing%20the%20valuable%20lessons%20that%20the%20inquiry%20has%20learned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInquiries%20are%20meant%20to%20inform%20political%20responses%20to%20crises%20through%20their%20recommendations.%20Because%20of%20this%2C%20governments%20often%20claim%20they%20cannot%20address%20the%20issues%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1111%2F1468-5973.00177%3Fcasa_token%3DQ6ZCEjqjqs0AAAAA%253AQ7pj8qvW9FFgxiXPIdbMLi5Prs8iNt4LGZGZu_VcZx1SLcfpLcPt0kwEQAUNf4eQjj6-68FY4Ppk%5C%22%3Euntil%20the%20inquiry%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E.%20More%20cynically%2C%20inquiries%20are%20sometimes%20alleged%20to%20kick%20issues%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbristoluniversitypressdigital.com%2Fview%2Fjournals%2Fpp%2F35%2F4%2Farticle-p629.xml%5C%22%3Einto%20the%20long%20grass%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20they%20take%20so%20long%20to%20report%20their%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20release%20of%20the%20ITV%20dramatisation%20has%20prompted%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.uk%2Fgovernment%2Fnews%2Fgovernment-to-quash-wrongful-post-office-convictions%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DHundreds%2520of%2520innocent%2520postmasters%2520who%2Cbrought%2520forward%2520by%2520the%2520government.%5C%22%3Egovernment%20to%20legislate%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20matters%20of%20compensation%20and%20exoneration%20for%20postmasters%20immediately.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20risks%20preempting%20the%20inquiry%E2%80%99s%20findings%2C%20which%20are%20likely%20to%20address%20these%20issues.%20Without%20taking%20account%20of%20the%20inquiry%E2%80%99s%20report%2C%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20response%20may%20not%20be%20as%20good%20as%20it%20could%20be.%20It%20is%20also%20possible%20that%20the%20inquiry%E2%80%99s%20findings%20might%20more%20fundamentally%20contradict%20what%20the%20government%20chooses%20to%20do%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22440%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FzPkvYXufpAY%3Fwmode%3Dtransparent%26start%3D0%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22260%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMedia%20coverage%20of%20miscarriages%20of%20justice%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20explosion%20of%20public%20attention%20on%20the%20Post%20Office%20scandal%20shows%20that%20media%20coverage%20can%20shape%20how%20similar%20scandals%20are%20investigated%20and%20responded%20to.%20Victims%20of%20the%20Horizon%20IT%20scandal%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fuk-england-merseyside-67867045%5C%22%3Ewelcomed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20increased%20attention%20that%20the%20ITV%20drama%20has%20brought.%20Others%20have%20asked%20why%20it%20has%20taken%20a%20television%20drama%20to%20finally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fcommentisfree%2F2024%2Fjan%2F08%2Falan-bates-post-office-victims-horizon-scandal%5C%22%3Espark%20action%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20long-running%20miscarriages%20of%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20affected%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fcommentisfree%2F2024%2Fjan%2F16%2Fpost-office-victims-windrush-families-trust-politicians%5C%22%3Eother%20scandals%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20expressed%20frustration%20that%20the%20government%20appears%20much%20less%20interested%20in%20acting%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fuk-news%2F2024%2Fjan%2F10%2Finfected-blood-scandal-victims-families-call-for-action-amid-post-office-injustice%5C%22%3Esecure%20justice%20for%20them%3C%2Fa%3E.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20contaminated%20blood%20scandal%2C%20in%20which%20thousands%20of%20people%20with%20bleeding%20disorders%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhaemophilia.org.uk%2Fpublic-inquiry%2Fthe-infected-blood-inquiry%2Fthe-contaminated-blood-scandal%2F%5C%22%3Ewere%20infected%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20HIV%20and%20hepatitis%20through%20the%20use%20of%20contaminated%20clotting%20factors%20in%20the%201970s%20and%2080s.%20This%20scandal%20also%20involves%20significant%20harm%20and%20loss%20of%20life%2C%20and%20affected%20far%20more%20people%20than%20the%20Post%20Office%20scandal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20that%20case%2C%20which%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20been%20depicted%20on%20television%2C%20the%20government%20has%20appeared%20much%20more%20willing%20to%20rely%20on%20a%20slow-moving%2C%20delayed%20public%20inquiry%20as%20the%20means%20of%20responding%20to%20the%20scandal%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fcommentisfree%2F2023%2Fjul%2F29%2Fcontaminated-blood-rishi-sunak-compensation-scheme%5C%22%3Edetermining%20how%20victims%20are%20compensated%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20current%20inquiry%20into%20the%20contaminated%20blood%20scandal%20is%20itself%20the%20second%20investigation%20of%20the%20issue%2C%20has%20been%20in%20progress%20since%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.infectedbloodinquiry.org.uk%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2FInquiry%2520Milestones.pdf%5C%22%3E2017%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20release%20of%20the%20final%20report%20has%20been%20delayed%20until%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.infectedbloodinquiry.org.uk%2Fnews%2Fpublication-inquiry-report-0%5C%22%3EMay%202024%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5