ine%20to%20the%20Union.%20But%20an%20effective%20impact%20requires%20meeting%20common%20man%E2%80%99s%20daily%20needs%20and%20providing%20them%20financial%20resources%20for%20the%20basic%20necessities%20of%20life.%20Health%20(and%20this%20includes%20nutrition)%20being%20a%20state%20subject%2C%20the%20recent%20announcement%20by%20the%20Centre%20to%20provide%20free%20food%20grains%20to%20nearly%2080%20crore%20people%20is%20clearly%20part%20of%20this%20trend.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20was%20adopted%2C%20it%20had%20been%20decided%20that%20powers%20of%20the%20states%20and%20the%20Centre%20to%20legislate%20on%20various%20subjects%20will%20be%20delineated.%20These%20were%20mentioned%20separately%20in%20the%20Central%20List%2C%20State%20List%20and%20the%20Concurrent%20List%20of%20Schedule%20VII%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20The%20Union%20government%20could%20legislate%20on%20items%20given%20in%20the%20Central%20List%20while%20state%20could%20do%20so%20for%20items%20in%20the%20State%20List.%20In%20the%20Concurrent%20List%20both%20could%20legislate%20but%20the%20Central%20legislation%20had%20overriding%20powers.%20Increasingly%2C%20the%20powers%20of%20the%20Centre%20have%20increased%2C%20with%20restriction%20on%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20power%20to%20frame%20laws.%20Under%20the%2042nd%20amendment%20to%20the%20Constitution%2C%20five%20subjects%20including%20education%20and%20forests%20were%20transferred%20to%20the%20Concurrent%20List%20from%20the%20State%20List%2C%20thereby%20restricting%20the%20power%20of%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20300px)%2085vw%2C%20300px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03150954%2FPrism.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03150954%2FPrism.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03150954%2FPrism-150x150.png%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691446%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%3EThe%20Indian%20Constitution%20mentions%20that%20the%20country%20is%20a%20Union%20of%20States.%20However%2C%20considering%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20country%20and%20its%20multifarious%20needs%2C%20it%20had%20given%20an%20overriding%20power%20under%20Article%203%20of%20the%20Constitution%20to%20Centre%20with%20the%20approval%20of%20Parliament%20to%20redraw%20the%20boundaries%20of%20states.%20Many%20new%20states%20were%20reorganised%20under%20this%20provision%2C%20the%20most%20recent%20being%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Uttarakhand%20and%20Telangana%2C%20redrawing%20the%20boundaries%20of%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20Andhra%20Pradesh.%20This%20was%20done%20after%20consultation%20with%20state%20governments%20and%20their%20assemblies%20had%20passed%20a%20resolution.%20The%20new%20entities%20created%20were%20full-fledged%20states.%20They%20have%20an%20assembly%20and%20exercise%20all%20the%20powers%20of%20any%20other%20state%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reorganisation%20of%20the%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20however%2C%20was%20done%20differently.%20Two%20union%20territories%20were%20created%20from%20the%20original%20state%3A%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20and%20Ladakh.%20The%20union%20territories%20under%20our%20Constitution%20are%20administered%20by%20the%20Centre.%20They%20may%20or%20may%20not%20have%20a%20state%20assembly.%20But%20these%20do%20not%20exercise%20the%20powers%20under%20the%20State%20List%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20Effectively%2C%20these%20are%20fully%20administered%20by%20Union%20government.%20There%20are%20questions%20that%20if%20the%20Union%20government%20can%20do%20this%20to%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20what%20is%20to%20prevent%20it%20from%20converting%20or%20bifurcating%20or%20trifurcating%20other%20states%20and%20converting%20these%20in%20to%20union%20territories%3F%20It%20also%20seems%20to%20be%20against%20the%20law%20laid%20down%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EKesavananda%20Bharati%3C%2Fem%3E%20case%2C%20that%20the%20basic%20structure%20of%20the%20Constitution%20is%20sacrosanct%20and%20must%20be%20preserved.%20While%20our%20political%20process%20is%20sound%2C%20the%20decision%20on%20J%26amp%3BK%20is%20worrisome%20for%20the%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20Article%20280%20of%20our%20Constitution%2C%20there%20is%20a%20provision%20for%20the%20constitution%20of%20a%20Finance%20Commission%20every%20five%20years.%20It%20assesses%20the%20resources%20of%20the%20Centre%20and%20different%20states%20and%20makes%20recommendation%20on%20transfer%20of%20funds%20to%20states%20based%20on%20a%20normative%20assessment.%20Since%20states%20have%20inadequate%20resources%2C%20the%20Centre%20makes%20devolution.%20This%20is%20to%20meet%20the%20requirements%20of%20health%20and%20education%2C%20apart%20from%20other%20financial%20needs.%20Similar%20arrangements%20exists%20in%20other%20federations%20like%20Australia%20and%20Canada.%20They%20have%20institutional%20arrangement%20for%20transfer%20of%20funds%20from%20the%20Central%20government%20based%20on%20well-specified%20norms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Growing%20Financial%20Curbs%C2%A0Leave%20States%20Struggling%20for%20Autonomy%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fstates-curbs-financial-autonomy-federalism%5C%22%3EGrowing%20Financial%20Curbs%C2%A0Leave%20States%20Struggling%20for%20Autonomy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20our%20Finance%20Commission%20transfers%20continue%20as%20contemplated%20in%20the%20Constitution%2C%20the%20Centre%20is%20gradually%20providing%20large%20funds%20outside%20it%20and%20encroaching%20on%20the%20remit%20of%20the%20states.%20Basic%20necessities%20like%20drinking%20water%2C%20housing%2C%20nutrition%20and%20poverty%20alleviation%20are%20areas%20where%20the%20states%20needs%20supplemental%20funds%20from%20the%20Centre%20for%20their%20own%20schemes.%20But%20in%20many%20areas%2C%20the%20Centre%20is%20has%20its%20own%20policies%20backed%20by%20funds.%20The%20states%20have%20to%20follow%20this%20if%20they%20wants%20Central%20funds.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20funds%20are%20directly%20being%20transferred%20to%20the%20beneficiary%20account.%20The%20states%2C%20being%20near%20the%20point%20of%20delivery%20of%20services%2C%20are%20better%20placed%20to%20provide%20them.%20They%20are%20the%20ones%20who%20look%20to%20the%20last%20mile%20connectivity.%20A%20result%20of%20the%20Centre%20entering%20this%20field%20is%20that%20criticism%20because%20of%20poor%20delivery%20is%20faced%20by%20the%20states%2C%20who%20provide%20the%20services%20at%20the%20ground%20level.%20The%20credit%20for%20the%20scheme%20invariably%20goes%20to%20the%20Centre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETake%20for%20instance%20nutrition.%20The%20health%20of%20citizens%2C%20including%20children%2C%20is%20the%20prime%20responsibility%20of%20the%20state%20government.%20Since%20the%20Centre%20does%20the%20public%20procurement%20of%20food%20grains%2C%20it%20can%20help%20by%20providing%20to%20the%20states%20enough%20financial%20resources%20and%20food%20grains%20to%20be%20given%20to%20the%20needy.%20Since%20there%20are%20a%20large%20number%20of%20people%20who%20may%20require%20support%2C%20the%20funds%20required%20would%20be%20large%20if%20free%20or%20subsidised%20food%20grains%20are%20to%20be%20given.%20With%20the%20passing%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Food%20Act%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20started%20this%20process.%20Recent%20reports%20indicate%20that%20about%2080%20core%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fin-another-sign-of-deep-economic-distress-modi-says-free-ration-to-800-million-to-continue%5C%22%3Ewill%20be%20given%20free%20food%20grains%20for%20some%20more%20time%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20all%20this%20is%20being%20done%20under%20the%20name%20of%20a%20Central%20initiative.%20Any%20deviation%20or%20additional%20support%20from%20the%20state%20is%20frowned%20upon.%20The%20entire%20approach%20is%20that%20it%20is%20a%20Central%20initiative%20and%20they%20are%20its%20architects.%20Being%20a%20state%20subject%2C%20this%20should%20have%20been%20left%20to%20states%20with%20each%20state%20adding%20or%20varying%20as%20it%20wished.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20important%20basic%20necessity%20is%20drinking%20water.%20This%20is%20clearly%20within%20the%20remit%20of%20the%20state.%20Since%20there%20may%20be%20support%20required%20in%20some%20difficult%20areas%2C%20the%20Centre%20can%20pitch%20in.%20But%20one%20finds%20announcement%20from%20Central%20leaders%20that%20every%20house%20will%20have%20piped%20water%20by%20a%20certain%20date.%20This%20function%20is%20to%20be%20undertaken%20by%20local%20bodies%3A%20panchayat%2C%20municipal%20boards%20or%20development%20authorities.%20It%20is%20the%20states%20who%20should%20lead%20the%20campaign%20and%20take%20credit%20or%20discredit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22A%20Short%20History%20of%20the%20Modi%20Government's%20Recent%20Attempts%20to%20Enter%20State%20Preserves%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmodi-government-centre-state-concurrent-list%5C%22%3EA%20Short%20History%20of%20the%20Modi%20Government%E2%80%99s%20Recent%20Attempts%20to%20Enter%20State%20Preserves%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuccessive%20governments%20in%20the%20country%20have%20tried%20to%20handle%20the%20question%20of%20poverty.%20While%20the%20Central%20government%20makes%20overarching%20economic%20policies%2C%20states%20try%20to%20promote%20investment%20and%20work%20on%20policies%20to%20create%20employment.%20Considering%20the%20vast%20rural%20areas%20in%20our%20country%2C%20improving%20incomes%20of%20farmers%20and%20agricultural%20productivity%20is%20very%20critical.%20Agriculture%20is%20a%20state%20subject.%20It%20is%20the%20states%20who%20have%20the%20responsibility%20to%20see%20that%20farmers%20in%20their%20area%20are%20able%20to%20earn%20enough%20money%20with%20better%20irrigation%20facilities%20and%20technical%20advice.%20It%20is%20they%20who%20should%20be%20providing%20them%20money%20when%20in%20distress.%20Interestingly%2C%20the%20Centre%20has%20promised%20to%20double%20their%20incomes.%20To%20better%20connect%20with%20the%20farmers%2C%20money%20is%20being%20transferred%20directly%20into%20the%20accounts%20of%20farmers%20under%20a%20Central%20scheme.%20This%20clearly%20is%20an%20encroachment%20over%20states%E2%80%99%20domain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Canadian%20and%20Australian%20federations%2C%20we%20notice%20that%20two%20approaches%20have%20guided%20the%20horizontal%20devolution%20of%20funds%20to%20different%20states.%20First%2C%20in%20the%20area%20of%20health%2C%20funds%20were%20transferred%20to%20different%20states%20to%20keep%20health%20facilities%20comparable%20amongst%20the%20states.%20Second%2C%20in%20the%20area%20of%20education%2C%20there%20was%20transfer%20with%20a%20similar%20objective.%20But%20having%20devolved%20the%20funds%2C%20it%20is%20left%20to%20the%20states%20to%20manage%20their%20institutions%20and%20health%20or%20education%20of%20their%20residents.%20The%20Government%20in%20India%20is%20more%20involved%20directly%20in%20these%20sectors.%20Especially%20in%20health%2C%20there%20are%20Central%20schemes%20like%20Ayushman%20Bharat.%20More%20and%20more%20coverage%20is%20given%20to%20a%20large%20number%20of%20people%20to%20avail%20of%20its%20benefits%20and%20make%20use%20of%20private%20hospitals.%20The%20impression%20which%20it%20gives%20is%20that%20the%20Centre%20is%20providing%20funds%20for%20it%20and%20is%20directly%20involved%20in%20it.%20It%20is%20the%20domain%20of%20the%20states%20but%20there%20is%20a%20massive%20involvement%20of%20the%20Centre%20in%20health%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHousing%20is%20another%20area%20where%20the%20Centre%20has%20made%20announcements%20like%20%E2%80%98housing%20for%20all%E2%80%99%20in%20a%20certain%20span%20of%20time.%20Land%20is%20clearly%20a%20state%20subject.%20Housing%20facilities%20especially%20pucca%20houses%20are%20planned%20by%20the%20states.%20Many%20of%20them%20have%20schemes%20for%20it.%20But%20the%20Centre%20wants%20to%20emphasise%20that%20it%20is%20cognisant%20of%20this%20basic%20necessity.%20There%20are%20reports%20in%20the%20media%20mentioning%20a%20timeframe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20defence%20and%20foreign%20policy%2C%20which%20are%20the%20remit%20of%20the%20Centre%2C%20are%20very%20important%20areas%20for%20a%20country%20in%20the%20international%20arena%2C%20they%20are%20less%20important%20for%20a%20common%20man.%20For%20him%2C%20an%20increase%20in%20income%2C%20healthcare%20facilities%2C%20a%20pucca%20house%20for%20his%20family%20and%20drinking%20water%20are%20very%20important.%20He%20is%20interested%20in%20jobs%20and%20some%20money%20in%20his%20bank%20to%20supplement%20his%20income.%20He%20needs%20communication%20in%20his%20village.%20Many%20of%20these%20areas%20are%20under%20the%20domain%20of%20states.%20Instead%20of%20transferring%20money%20to%20the%20states%20to%20let%20them%20plan%20it%2C%20the%20Centre%20puts%20in%20its%20funds%20directly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Centre%20is%20entering%20these%20areas%20by%20way%20of%20its%20various%20schemes.%20The%20functions%20which%20were%20basically%20of%20states%20have%20the%20Centre%20playing%20a%20key%20role.%20It%20can%20be%20argued%20that%20many%20Central%20initiatives%20are%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20the%20common%20man.%20But%20in%20a%20federal%20structure%20this%20is%20difficult%20to%20accept.%20The%20Centre%20and%20the%20states%20must%20act%20in%20accordance%20with%20legislative%20competence%20and%20the%20spirit%20of%20federalism.%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20with%20the%20reduction%20in%20the%20State%20List%20and%20expansion%20of%20the%20Central%20List%2C%20the%20legislative%20competence%20of%20states%20has%20been%20restricted.%20The%20recent%20creation%20of%20two%20UTs%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20has%20given%20states%20cause%20for%20worry.%20The%20deployment%20of%20large%20Central%20funds%20in%20areas%20which%20are%20essentially%20of%20states%20further%20encroaches%20on%20their%20power.%20The%20division%20of%20legislative%20powers%20is%20now%20getting%20blurred.%20This%20is%20not%20healthy%20for%20a%20long%20term%20growth%20and%20stability%20of%20our%20federal%20structure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EB.K.%20Chaturvedi%20is%20a%20former%20Cabinet%20Secretary%20and%20Member%20of%20the%20Planning%20Commission%20and%2013th%20Finance%20Commission.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705994738000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F23120936%2Fmarkus-spiske-IiEFmIXZWSw-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fhow-the-union-govt-is-slowly-but-surely-blurring-indias-federal-structure%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Responsibilities%20of%20the%20state%20governments%20are%20being%20slowly%20overtaken%20by%20the%20Centre%2C%20keen%20as%20it%20is%20to%20take%20credit%20for%20all%20welfare%20programmes.%20Meanwhile%2C%20state%20coffers%20are%20not%20getting%20the%20assistance%20they%20need%20from%20the%20Union%20government.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fhow-the-union-govt-is-slowly-but-surely-blurring-indias-federal-structure%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ayesha%20on%20being%20linked%20to%20Shoaib%20Malik%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705994614000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107075367%2Cimgsize-27450.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fayesha-omars-nightmare-being-linked-with-shoaib-malik-and-suffering-panic-attacks%2Farticleshow%2F107075367.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20