%20slurs%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20change%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20gone%20unnoticed%20by%20professor%20Anil%20Kumar%20Singh%20who%20was%20a%20Masters%20student%20in%201992.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20way%20Muslims%20are%20being%20alienated%20in%20society%20hides%20the%20fact%20that%20theywere%20more%20than%20happy%20for%20the%20Ram%20temple%20to%20be%20built.%20But%20this%20temple%20now%20is%20a%20VHP-RSS%20project%3B%20it%20is%20not%20a%20temple%20for%20Hindus%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESingh%20mentions%20Sheetla%20Singh%20who%20was%20a%20veteran%20journalist%20and%20writer%20from%20Faizabad.%20He%20has%20written%20the%20book%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAyodhya%3A%20The%20Truth%20of%20Ram%20Janmabhoomi-Babri%20Masjid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20events%20of%20Indian%20politics%2C%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20demolition%20on%20December%206%2C%201992%20and%20the%20Ram%20Janmabhoomi%20movement.%20In%20the%20book%20he%20has%20given%20details%20of%20how%20the%20leaders%20of%20the%20Muslim%20community%20had%20taken%20the%20initiative%20for%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20Ram%20temple%2C%20but%20that%20this%20was%20not%20in%20the%20Sangh%E2%80%99s%20political%20interests.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F23093848%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-01-19-at-21.25.01-e1705983017190.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F23093848%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-01-19-at-21.25.01-e1705983017190.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F23093848%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-01-19-at-21.25.01-e1705983017190-300x200.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F23093848%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-01-19-at-21.25.01-e1705983017190-1024x684.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-694078%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22801%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAyodhya.%20Photo%3A%20Afaq%20Ullah%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EChanging%20times%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEarlier%2C%20Faizabad%20and%20Ayodhya%20were%20two%20separate%20municipalities.%20The%20Faizabad%20station%20was%20bigger%20and%20there%20was%20only%20a%2010-12%20km%20distance%20between%20the%20two%20stations.%20After%20Adityanath%20came%20to%20power%2C%20in%20his%20renaming%20drive%2C%20Faizabad%20station%20was%20renamed%20%E2%80%98Ayodhya%20Cantonment%E2%80%99%20and%20Ayodhya%20was%20called%20%E2%80%98Ayodhya%20Dham%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIts%20a%20city%20built%20near%20Sarayu%20river%2C%20it%20was%20beautiful%20and%20calm.%20I%20used%20to%20go%20to%20Ayodhya%20many%20times%20during%20my%20college%20days.%20Now%20it%20has%20become%20glamorised%20and%20commercial%20and%20is%20no%20longer%20the%20serene%20Ayodhya%20town.%20Everything%20old%20is%20being%20broken%20down%2C%E2%80%9D%20Afaq%20says%2C%20reminiscing%20the%20old%20times.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfaq%20has%20decided%20to%20become%20the%20chronicler%20of%20the%20times%20and%20has%20been%20collecting%20newspaper%20clippings%20for%20the%20last%2015%20days.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20next%2010-20%20years%2C%20if%20a%20student%20or%20journalist%20comes%2C%20I%20can%20show%20them%20what%20the%20local%20newspapers%20are%20printing.%20Six%20out%20of%20eight%20pages%20are%20devoted%20to%20Ram%20temple-related%20news%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMany%20argue%20for%20the%20tourism%20and%20job%20opportunities%20in%20the%20religious%20city.%20Afaq%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CYes%2C%20infrastructure%20has%20been%20built.%20Everything%20is%20grand%20now.%20But%20who%20will%20be%20able%20to%20afford%20an%20organised%20tourism%20company%2C%20travel%20agencies%2C%20hotel%20industries%2C%20etc%3F%20Definitely%20not%20the%20locals%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EProfessor%20Singh%20says%20that%20in%201992%2C%20when%20the%20Masjid%20was%20demolished%20by%20people%20from%20outside%20the%20city%2C%20locals%20had%20understood%20that%20it%20was%20a%20political%20ploy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20was%20a%20deep%20understanding%20and%20feeling%20of%20brotherhood%20among%20communities.%20BJP%20even%20lost%20elections%20after%20the%20demolition.%20But%20post-Babri%20generations%20have%20only%20seen%20RSS%20and%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eandolans%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20There%20is%20no%20sense%20of%20history%20now.%20The%20youth%20now%20says%2C%20%E2%80%98Where%20will%20our%20temple%20be%20built%20if%20not%20at%20Ayodhya%3F%E2%80%99.%20It%20is%20being%20showcased%20as%20the%20Hindu%20renaissance%20and%20hatred%20has%20spread%20everywhere%2C%E2%80%9D%20Singh%20adds.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESwati%20Krishna%20is%20an%C2%A0activist%20and%20political%20observer.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705991201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F23093839%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-01-19-at-21.24.54.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fayodhya-land-wealth-babri-masjid-ram-temple%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20is%20common%20knowledge%20that%20land%20has%20been%20usurped%20by%20the%20VHP-RSS%20combine%20and%20that%20wealth%20has%20gone%20to%20the%20rich%20in%20the%20name%20of%20development.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fayodhya-land-wealth-babri-masjid-ram-temple%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22