%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Pastor%20Mahananda%20fell%20unconscious%2C%20and%20his%20family%20took%20him%20to%20a%20local%20Samudayik%20Swasthya%20Kendra%2C%20from%20where%20he%20was%20referred%20to%20Holy%20Cross%20Hospital%20in%20Kunkuri.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20one%20Naresh%20Kumar%20Yadav%20and%20several%20others%20who%20were%20named%20as%20accused%20in%20Shiv%E2%80%99s%20FIR%2C%20have%20also%20filed%20an%20FIR%20against%20Shiv%20and%20others%2C%20claiming%20that%20they%20were%20just%20on%20their%20way%20with%20items%20of%20puja.%20The%20FIR%20also%20states%20that%20they%20questioned%20the%20pastor%20and%20others%20about%20their%20identity%20and%20why%20they%20had%20come%20to%20the%20village%20and%20in%20return%2C%20were%20pelted%20with%20stones.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20United%20Christian%20Forum%20report%20has%20it%20that%20violence%20against%20Christians%20occurred%20in%2023%20states%20in%202023.%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20leads%20with%20155%20incidents%2C%20followed%20by%20Chhattisgarh%20with%2084%20incidents.%20Christian%20community%20members%20told%20The%20Wire%20that%20last%20week%20alone%20five%20pastors%20had%20been%20beaten%20up%20by%20a%20Hindutva%20group%20in%20the%20Jashpur%20area.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Chhattisgarh%20Christian%20Forum%20has%20also%20said%20that%20on%20January%2021%2C%20in%20the%20Kundra%20village%2C%20people%20entered%20the%20local%20pastor%E2%80%99s%20house%2C%20verbally%20abused%20him%2C%20and%20planted%20saffron%20flags%20at%20his%20house.%20They%20allegedly%20threatened%20him%20with%20dire%20consequences%20if%20he%20did%20not%20convert%20to%20Hinduism.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705988407000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2F22123737%2F2EE156B8-BC97-409A-B416-F1328599EE19.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fchhattisgarh-comm