E2%80%99t%20Someone%E2%80%99s%20Property%3A%20What%20Opposition%20Leaders%20Said%20on%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20Event%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F22212245%2Fimage-1784.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESome%20opposition%20leaders%20responded%20strongly%20to%20the%20inauguration%20of%20the%20Ram%20Temple%2C%20on%20January%2022%20(Monday)%2C%20expressing%20concerns%20over%20the%20blurring%20lines%20between%20religion%20and%20politics.%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20video%20statement%2C%20Kerala%20chief%20minister%20Pinarayi%20Vijayan%20said%20religion%20is%20a%20private%20affair%20and%20that%20the%20constitution%20has%20minced%20no%20words%20in%20stating%20that%20all%20persons%20are%20equally%20entitled%20to%20the%20right%20to%20freely%20profess%2C%20practice%20and%20propagate%20religion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSecularism%20is%20the%20soul%20of%20the%20country.%20It%20has%20been%20part%20of%20our%20identity%20as%20a%20nation%20right%20from%20the%20days%20of%20our%20national%20movement.%20Those%20belonging%20to%20different%20states%20and%20those%20not%20part%20of%20any%20religion%20had%20taken%20part%20in%20the%20freedom%20struggle.%20This%20nation%20belongs%20to%20all%20people%20and%20all%20sections%20of%20Indian%20society%20in%20equal%20measure.%20As%20those%20who%20have%20taken%20an%20oath%20to%20uphold%20the%20Constitution%2C%20we%20ought%20to%20ensure%20that%20every%20person%20within%20our%20territories%20enjoys%20these%20rights.%20We%20cannot%20be%20promoting%20one%20religion%20above%20all%20others%2C%E2%80%9D%20Vijayan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20a%20major%20departure%20from%20our%20times%20when%20our%20constitutional%20office%20bearers%20have%20been%20cautious%20from%20taking%20part%20in%20religious%20events%20as%20it%20would%20cast%20aspersions%20on%20our%20credentials%20as%20a%20secular